Date: 17/9/1881
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition: 7
Quote: The fence I propose is much in use in the North Island, and is called a stab fence, composed of heart stakes six feet long and four by one battens, and the manner of erecting it is as follows:- Open a trench one foot six inches deep, taking care to undermine it slightly at the side on which the stakes are placed upright, fill in the trench, and nail on the batten four inches from the top.
